beer_description:
Look: A golden straw colour, with a strong foam once opened then the bubbles gently rise to the top and a good head remains.

Nose: Sharp, lively and nervous, fermentation with a touch reminiscent of a flowery cheese.

In the mouth: A round, balance and full flavour. In the mouth it is floral, elegant and direct, almost feminine. A great beer that perfectly suits cheeses with a hard crust or some fine Bries and Camemberts.
The aftertaste has a noble bitterness.

Cask ABV: 3.8%
Bottle ABV: 4.2% 
A golden beer whose aroma is dominated by hops that give characteristic citrus notes. Hops and fruit on the palate are balanced by malt and a bitter base. Dry hoppy finish with soft fruit flavors. A nationally respected ale, winner of numerous awards, JHB is a blond baby packed with flavour & perfect for those long sessions as well as a quick pint at lunchtime. This popular beer was crowned Champion beer of britain in the bitter category in 2001 and 1999. 
Challenger and American Mount Hood hops.

This recipe is a true craft ale brewed with only water, yeast, hops and malted barley, in keeping with the Bavarian Purity Law of 1516. We have designed it with a vibrant golden amber hue and a refreshing body. The mild addition of Kent Golding hops balances the generous amounts of caramel malts to give it a malty rather than a bitter finish. A special strain of California Ale Yeast gives the brew a slight hint of fruity aroma.

Highly hopped full-flavored beer based on the ?American Pale Ale? style but with more malt flavor. With American-grown hops and barley malted right here in good ol? Wisconsin. This beer will make even the most discerning tongue tingle.

Crowned the official drink by King Friedrich August III of Saxony, Radeberger, a pilsner style beer brewed near Dresden, is characterized by its dazzling and refreshing taste and has long been enjoyed by German nobility.

Our K?lsch is a classic golden ale that uses a centuries old yeast strain sourced from a famous K?lsch brewer in K?ln, Germany. Fermented at 62 degrees, then cold conditioned, it has the delicate fruity aroma of an ale with the crisp, clean finish of a lager. It is brewed with lightly roasted malt and 100% German Noble Hops: Perle for bitterness and Hallertau Traditional for flavor and aroma.

Named Cinq Cents in 75 cl (25.4 fl.oz.) bottles, this beer, with its typical golden color, slightly hazy appearance and fine head, is especially characterized by its aroma which results from an agreeable combination of fresh hops and yeast.

It was first brewed by the monks of Chimay at Scourmont Abbey in 1966.

Above all it is the fruity notes of muscat and raisins that give this beer a particularly attractive aroma.

beer_description: Redhook Sunrye, a light, refreshing summer beer brewed with six barley malts, including a touch of organic rye. The opalescent golden color of Sunrye is a result of its unfiltered nature. Light and crisp, this brew was made for slaking summer thirsts.
Golden unfiltered "wheat" beer. Smooth quality with hints of banana and cloves with a spicy finish.
A full-bodied dark mahogany beer, with a rich malty texture. It is sparsely hopped, in the traditional Munich style.
A malty, aromatic and hoppy mixture. Copper colored, this beer is medium bodied and full of flavor. Vienna Style.

A light, crisp and traditionally hoppy beer with a soft palate and flowery bouquet. Light, both in color and taste. "Classic" Old World beer that will be most familiar to the individual who prefers domestic beers.
Black Wych is a beguiling traditional English dark stout, silky smooth, soft and seductive. A heady brew, which entices you to lose your senses and fall for the charms of The Black Wych.

This beautifully copper colored beer has a bold flavor and aroma distinctive to the four varieties of hops used in its brewing. Columbus, Falconers Flight, Amarillo and no Cascade. A true American Pale Ale.

beer_name: K?nig Ludwig Weissbier Hell / Royal Bavarian Hefe-Weizen

beer_description: Brewmaster's Collection Special Reserve Ale uses Saccharomyces and Brettanomyces Yeasts

A very drinkable, bitter, and malty Extra Special Bitter.  Pretty true to style.  Irish Ale Malt base with some toasted character from the Victory Malt.  Also a touch of Caramel / reddish hue from Caramel 80 malt.  Strong bitterness from Nugget hops plus Norther Brewer and Fuggle later in the boil.  Generous late hop additions of Fuggle and a touch of Amarillo to give it a slight American twist.

Point Belgian White is a smooth refreshing and distinctive beer brewed in the tradition of Belgian Style White Ales. Our recipe boasts the finest barley and wheat malts, white wheat, rolled oats, and Noble Hallertau and Saaz hops - naturally flavored with a hint of Curacao orange peel and coriander. The result is a light-bodied beer renowned for its signature golden-white haze. Try it with an orange slice.

Named after the cream colored bricks used to build Milwaukee, this amber pale ale is tasty year round. Pours a light amber with a frothy, stable white head. The light citrus, grapefruit nose comes from American hop varieties, while caramel malts lend a backbone to their crisp, balanced bitterness. Finishes smooth with mild hop flavor.
35 IBU
Full malty flavor with highlights of chocolate and light roast. Cascade, Columbus, and Mt. Hood hops yield a uniquely American character to this beer.
A very distinct flavor is imparted to this lager from the copious use of Nobel Czech Saaz hops. This process provides a noticable bitterness in a lighter golden beer.

Made with generous amounts of west coast hops, our Pale Ale boasts a fragrant aroma and a pleasant hop bite. It has a deep golden color, and nicely balances the bitterness of the hops with the sweetness of the malt. Whether you know hops or not, our Pale Ale will appeal to all those looking for a refreshing, well balanced ale.

Alcohol %: 5.4
Carbohydrates: 0
Calories: 0
Sold as Spaten Premium Lager in the U.S. and Spaten M?nchen in the U.K.
beer_name: Spaten M?nchen / M?nchner Hell / Premium Lager

beer_description: Up until the Second World War, dark beer was the predominant beer type in the Munich area. The hard water found in the region played a special role in producing this specialty. In his book ?Beer International?, the world-renowned English beer writer, Michael Jackson, accurately describes the Ayinger ?Altbairisch Dunkel? as: ?A good example of its kind. Impenetrably dark with a golden-brown gleam when held up to the light, and with a warm aroma and malty taste, while summoning up coffee taste sensations on going down. It is brewed from five types of malt (two of which are torrified dark), and it is only lightly hopped.? It is produced using the traditional double fermentation process.

In our golden-yellow crystal-clear wheat beer the fresh citrus flavour harmonises very well with spicy banana notes. The fine sparkling gives it a tangy and animated appearance. Throughout summer and winter, it?s a prickling experience. It goes well with fish, seafood, white meat or it can be enjoyed as an aperitif. Brewed according to our centuries-old brewing tradition on the Weihenstephan hill.
A Northern German (Friesian) Pilsener that is characteristic of the style. It is a little more hoppy than Czech pilseners giving it a more bitter ("herb" in German) flavour.

Franziskaner Hefe-Weissbier Naturtr?b ist ein nat?rlicher und eleganter Weissbierprotagonist aus Bayern mit einem ?ppig wei?en Schaum. Das kupfergoldene Weizenbier mit hefetr?ber Opaleszenz entfaltet einen aromatischen Duft mit harmonischer Frucht in dem Bananen und Zitrusfr?chte gr??en lassen.

Durch den h?heren Kohlens?uregehalt ist es besonders spritzig und perlend. Seinen unverwechselbaren besonders frischen, dezent w?rzigen und fruchtigen Geschmack mit mild-s??lichem Ausklang entfaltet Franziskaner Hefe-Weissbier Naturtr?b beim genussvollen Herunterschlucken.
Also brewed at 4.6% and 4.2% for other markets, eg. Scandinavia.

Braukunst ist die Kunst, mit den wenigen Zutaten, die das Reinheitsgebot und die K?lschkonvention vorgeben, etwas Besonderes zu schaffen. Reines Wasser aus eigenem Brunnen, oberg?rige Hefe aus eigener Reinzucht, bestes Gersten- und Weizenmalz und ausgesuchte Hopfensorten ? das Ergebnis daraus kann sich schmecken lassen: spritzig-frisch auf der Zunge, feinherb-hopfig am Gaumen, schlank-elegant im Abgang. Einfach guter Geschmack, der folgende Formen annehmen kann.
Edel und doch bodenst?ndig: mit dem unverwechselbar frisch-w?rzigen und echten Geschmack. Die norddeutsche Heimatmarke ? hergestellt nach dem deutschen Reinheitsgebot.
Note: The labelling of this beer varies by country, as does the ABV. The standard ABV is 4.7% but 4.5% and 4.8% have also been reported.
beer_name: Pilsener / Premium German Lager / Pilsener Herb-W?rzig

beer_description: 1664 Blanc is an original wheat beer. It is a different, fresh and fruity white beer, slightly bitter with hints of citrus and coriander spices. With its modern and elegant blue bottle, 1664 Blanc is perfectly adapted to all moments of conviviality.
The Ungespundete is our only type of beer that is made without the use of smoked malt. It is a bright, unfiltered beer with a fine aroma of hops and a low CO2 content.
